<paragraph id="7FC13B7D7875164DC7A87F001FC27FF6" pageId="5" pageNumber="172">
The pure red populations of the Kendevan region have been described as ssp. kendevanica Tremewan, 1977, and populations with the same phenotype are found further south-west to Zanjan (Figs 49-54). Similar pure red populations occur in the Van 
<normalizedToken id="6536E6115FDA085D120E8FC04A11AC00" originalValue="Gölü">Goelue</normalizedToken>
region in eastern Turkey (ssp. placida Bang-Haas, 1913), while the Zagros range, the Iranian Talysh and Azerbaijan-e Sharqi are predominantly inhabited by populations with mixed characters of yellow forewings and red hindwings (Figs 43-45) or yellow fore- and hindwings (Figs 40-42, 46-48). A unique character that distinguishes all of these populations of 
<taxonomicName id="9518B9A7ABDFDA7A8D3E69E0C830634F" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena tamara" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamara">Zygaena tamara</taxonomicName>
from all other 
<taxonomicName id="813FD4A183F010B08733CE1B5D465253" authority="Hübner, 1819" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1819" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Mesembrynus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesembrynus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesembrynus</taxonomicName>
species is the red abdominal cingulum that is present on two to three segments in the females and on three segments in the males (Figs 40-54, 63), a character that is in strong contrast to the newly discovered populations from the northern side of the Alborz range, which we here describe as 
<taxonomicName id="FB0E8E70927822EFED698D23AB9CF684" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena tamara" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="tamara" subSpecies="dailamica">Zygaena tamara dailamica</taxonomicName>
ssp. n.
</paragraph>
